# Keep the runtime image small: exclude local build artifacts and cruft.
# Dev-only artefacts that would ship stale bits into the container:
node_modules
dist
.mica-pids

# Python virtualenvs MUST be excluded. The voice install.sh creates
# scripts/voice/.venv during devcontainer setup; if that dir is left in
# the build context, `COPY . .` would ship a venv whose pyvenv.cfg bakes
# the devcontainer's absolute path (/workspaces/mica/...) and whose
# binaries are weeks stale relative to the rest of the image. install.sh
# would then skip its create step (idempotency guard) and force-reinstall
# only nvidia-cudnn-cu13, leaving torch from the devcontainer date and
# cuDNN from today — different builds, CUDNN_STATUS_SUBLIBRARY_VERSION_MISMATCH
# at runtime. Build always starts from a fresh venv.
**/.venv

# Source control / hidden state we don't need at runtime:
.git
.github

# Internal drafts and legacy docs — not needed at runtime:
internal

# OS cruft:
*.log
.DS_Store

# Note: .devcontainer/ is intentionally NOT excluded. It ships with the
# runtime image so users pulling the image still see how the dev image
# is built, for parity.
